This paper investigates the bias caused by the fault localization step in Automated Program Repair (APR) systems, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also proposes to highlight the impact of different fault localization configurations on APR systems, which involves analyzing the performance of these systems, a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the Defects4J benchmark, which is a dataset commonly used in software engineering research, and the potential misleading results when comparing APR systems, which is related to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR).
